<TITLE> DB arrests suspected Indian separatist </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com)  Detective Branch on Tuesday arrested a close associate of Jiban Singh, chief of the outlawed Kamtapur Liberation Organisation who is also suspected of stealing Rabindranath Tagore's Nobel Prize medal. Thirty-year-old Tapan Patwari, also known as Palash Dash, was arrested near a mosque in the capital's Hazaribagh area, Hazaribagh Police Station sub-inspector Ruhul Amin told bdnews24.com. A case was filed against him Tuesday afternoon for illegal entry into Bangladesh, Amin said. A DB police officer, requesting anonymity, said Tapan was Tapan is also alleged to be one of the top leaders of the outlawed KLO, fighting for a separate state for Rajbongshi tribals in the northern part of West Bengal, and wanted in the Tagore Nobel theft case. b
